context: On 30 March, Nasser proclaimed a manifesto stipulating the restoration of civil liberties, greater parliamentary <a3_0>independence<a3_0/> from the executive, major structural changes to the <a0_0>ASU<a0_0/>, and a campaign to rid the government of corrupt elements. A public referendum approved the proposed measures in May, and held subsequent elections for the Supreme Executive Committee, the ASU's highest decision-making body. Observers noted that the declaration signaled an important shift from political repression to <a1_0>liberalization<a1_0/>, although its promises would largely go <a2_0>unfulfilled<a2_0/>.
